1
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:24,166
[MARLYA]
To make a long story short,

2
00:00:24,250 --> 00:00:27,000
I've grown convinced
that I'm unlucky.

3
00:00:35,166 --> 00:00:38,000
[FREE]
In the end, I suppose I'm lucky.

4
00:00:38,083 --> 00:00:40,833
[RED HOOD growls]

5
00:00:40,916 --> 00:00:42,250
[FAIRY TECHNICIAN]
We'll remove the fairy organ

6
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:45,916
from Red Hood and surgically
implant it inside you.

7
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:51,125
[RED HOOD roars]

8
00:00:51,208 --> 00:00:52,458
[FREE gasps]

9
00:00:52,541 --> 00:00:54,250
[FAIRY TECHNICIAN]
You volunteered and were chosen

10
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:56,250
for the procedure based
on your capacity

11
00:00:56,333 --> 00:01:00,250
to become a Fairy Soldier.
This was your choice.

12
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:02,916
Glory to our kingdom of Ledrad.

13
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:06,375
And glory to our leader,
Majesty Olbany.

14
00:01:08,375 --> 00:01:09,333
[FREE grunts]

15
00:01:12,625 --> 00:01:15,250
[MARLYA] The person who
raised me ended up dying.


16
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:17,291
I had no one.


17
00:01:17,375 --> 00:01:19,416
As for my mother and father,


18
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:22,583
they both died
the day I was born.


19
00:01:22,666 --> 00:01:25,750
People called me
the "little disaster."

20
00:01:27,125 --> 00:01:32,416
[MARLYA] Anyone who gets close
to me meets a tragic end.

21
00:01:32,500 --> 00:01:34,708
I was born unlucky.

22
00:01:35,750 --> 00:01:38,583
[SOLDIERS shouting]

23
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:45,333
[RED FAIRY SOLDIER A groans]

24
00:01:49,208 --> 00:01:50,833
[FAIRY SOLDIERS grunting]

25
00:01:58,083 --> 00:02:00,083
Fire!

26
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:17,583
[RED SOLDIERS gasp, scream]

27
00:02:17,666 --> 00:02:18,875
[roars]

28
00:02:18,958 --> 00:02:20,125
[grunts]

29
00:02:22,708 --> 00:02:24,166
[FREE yelling]

30
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:27,791
[FREE grunts]

31
00:02:30,416 --> 00:02:31,416
[FREE groans]

32
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:37,916
[NORKA growls]

33
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,083
[screaming]

34
00:02:43,708 --> 00:02:46,125
For your crimes,

35
00:02:46,208 --> 00:02:47,916
you will bleed.

36
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,583
[WOLF]
No! Run!

37
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:01,458
[coughs]

38
00:03:05,041 --> 00:03:06,875
[JET panting]

39
00:03:11,291 --> 00:03:13,750
Jet! No!

40
00:03:25,708 --> 00:03:28,041
[FREE]
Don't die.

41
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:29,291
Wake up!

42
00:03:32,625 --> 00:03:34,416
[FREE]
This isn't real.

43
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:36,625
Come on, Jet, open your eyes!

44
00:03:36,708 --> 00:03:38,291
You're not dead!

45
00:03:38,375 --> 00:03:41,958
[FREE cries]

46
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:43,708
[FREE]
No denying it.

47
00:03:43,791 --> 00:03:45,958
I'm lucky all right.

48
00:03:46,041 --> 00:03:48,166
In the worst way possible.

49
00:05:35,541 --> 00:05:36,750
[MARLYA]
Mm...

50
00:05:36,833 --> 00:05:37,833
[CHIMA chirps]

51
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:51,000
[FREE whistles]

52
00:05:51,083 --> 00:05:53,250
[NEIN] To recap, your
year-long infiltration

53
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:56,541
into Gui Carlin ended in
failure, due to the appearance

54
00:05:56,625 --> 00:05:59,625
of a fairy-wielding
woman named Veronica.

55
00:05:59,708 --> 00:06:01,250
You then returned
with a young lady

56
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:04,000
who has ties to the
aforementioned woman.

57
00:06:04,083 --> 00:06:06,291
Is that the gist of it,
Free Underbar?

58
00:06:06,375 --> 00:06:07,916
Did I leave anything
important out?

59
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,625
[FREE] I'd say it's
an accurate summary.

60
00:06:10,708 --> 00:06:12,333
[NEIN]
Marlya Noel.

61
00:06:12,416 --> 00:06:16,958
In your report, you mention
she might be fairy-possessed.

62
00:06:17,041 --> 00:06:20,291
[FREE] Mm... Yes, however
there's no evidence

63
00:06:20,375 --> 00:06:23,750
she underwent a fairy organ
transplant like we did.

64
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,500
[FREE groaning]

65
00:06:37,291 --> 00:06:41,583
A fairy primordial directly
possessing a human host.

66
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:52,541
[NEIN]
It shouldn't be possible.

67
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:56,625
[FREE] Yet that seems to
be the only explanation.

68
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:58,166
Uh!

69
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:01,125
I'd rather this matter didn't
leave my office, understood?

70
00:07:01,208 --> 00:07:03,166
Your report will need
to be rewritten.

71
00:07:03,250 --> 00:07:04,750
[sighs]

72
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:07,541
[NEIN] You're not pleased with
your commanding officer's order?

73
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:09,541
I'll get right on it.

74
00:07:09,625 --> 00:07:11,416
[footsteps]

75
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:13,500
[door opens, closes]

76
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:14,958
[NEIN grunts]

77
00:07:24,083 --> 00:07:28,875
[IZEM] That's the limit as far
as this place is concerned.

78
00:07:28,958 --> 00:07:32,250
There aren't many customers
who place orders this large.

79
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:36,375
Good thing, too.

80
00:07:36,458 --> 00:07:37,875
Or there'd be war again.

81
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:39,916
I could do without
another war.

82
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,916
Hard enough surviving
the last one.

83
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,041
Though our profits
would skyrocket.

84
00:07:44,125 --> 00:07:45,583
Huh?

85
00:07:45,666 --> 00:07:47,708
See ya at the rendezvous
point then?

86
00:07:47,791 --> 00:07:48,958
[WOLF]
Yeah.

87
00:07:58,458 --> 00:07:59,333
Hey, Free.

88
00:07:59,416 --> 00:08:00,750
Mind if I open the window?

89
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:02,083
Go ahead.

90
00:08:09,875 --> 00:08:12,250
So you just wanted to
find this Veronica.

91
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:16,041
That was the only reason
for joining the mafia?

92
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:17,416
I guess.

93
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:19,625
Because she's a target
for Dorothea.

94
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:22,458
You realize that fact,
don't you?

95
00:08:22,541 --> 00:08:23,875
[MARLYA]
Regulation.

96
00:08:23,958 --> 00:08:26,541
But... If you choose to stick
with this line of work,

97
00:08:26,625 --> 00:08:29,208
I'm sure you'll run
into her again.

98
00:08:29,291 --> 00:08:32,291
[MARLYA]
Next time, it'll be as enemies.

99
00:08:40,541 --> 00:08:43,291
Veronica from Suna
is gone forever.

100
00:08:43,375 --> 00:08:44,833
Forget her.

101
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:49,375
[MARLYA]
I couldn't do that, Ver.

102
00:08:49,458 --> 00:08:50,750
Ever.

103
00:08:59,458 --> 00:09:01,000
[gasps]

104
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:02,666
How much further?

105
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,250
My poor backside...

106
00:09:04,333 --> 00:09:05,708
Did ya say something?

107
00:09:05,791 --> 00:09:07,375
Nothing at all!

108
00:09:07,458 --> 00:09:09,333
The Arcame mafia
deals extensively

109
00:09:09,416 --> 00:09:12,750
in artificial fairies. They're
even manufacturing them.

110
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:15,083
So, our mission is to
expose and take down

111
00:09:15,166 --> 00:09:16,750
their illegal operation?

112
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:17,916
[FREE]
According to our intel,

113
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,333
a large transaction
is occurring nearby.

114
00:09:20,416 --> 00:09:22,875
We want to secure the contraband
and identify the buyer.

115
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:25,250
Artificial fairies--
they're supposed to fight

116
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:26,500
in the place of humans?

117
00:09:26,583 --> 00:09:27,666
That's right.

118
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:30,166
But the War of Unification
ended years ago.

119
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:33,125
Why would anybody need them now?

120
00:09:33,208 --> 00:09:36,458
Makes you think there's a chance
the war never really ended.

121
00:10:12,291 --> 00:10:14,625
Oh! Welcome to
the observatory, sir.

122
00:10:14,708 --> 00:10:15,875
You too, Marlya.

123
00:10:15,958 --> 00:10:17,333
Any movement so far?

124
00:10:17,416 --> 00:10:18,583
I'm afraid not.

125
00:10:18,666 --> 00:10:21,083
Good to see you,
Mr. Tova. And...

126
00:10:21,166 --> 00:10:23,541
Quiet, please.
You're distracting.

127
00:10:24,458 --> 00:10:26,750
[SERGE] Heh, we should
do what she says.

128
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:28,958
You don't want to make
Klara angry, trust me.

129
00:10:29,041 --> 00:10:31,833
I'm a bit of an expert when
it comes to making her mad.

130
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:33,250
Still too loud.

131
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:35,625
What'd I say?
Soul-shaking. [laughs]

132
00:10:35,708 --> 00:10:37,208
Why're you laughing then?

133
00:10:37,291 --> 00:10:40,000
Oh, and by the way,
you can call me Serge.

134
00:10:40,083 --> 00:10:41,666
And as for her...

135
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:44,583
Klara will work just fine.

136
00:10:44,666 --> 00:10:45,791
[gasps]

137
00:10:45,875 --> 00:10:47,083
Here they come.

138
00:10:47,166 --> 00:10:48,125
[SERGE grunts]

139
00:10:53,625 --> 00:10:55,166
[creaking]

140
00:10:57,791 --> 00:11:00,250
[KLARA]
One person's getting out.

141
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:01,958
[FREE]
Can you see the cargo?

142
00:11:02,041 --> 00:11:03,125
[SERGE]
Looks like there's more coming.

143
00:11:03,208 --> 00:11:04,291
[gasps]

144
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:09,541
[FREE]
Three vehicles?

145
00:11:09,625 --> 00:11:11,708
Given their size, I'd say each
of those transports could hold

146
00:11:11,791 --> 00:11:14,875
ten artificial fairies.
Thirty total.

147
00:11:15,541 --> 00:11:17,041
[KLARA]
In the plaza!

148
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:24,250
[KLARA]
Someone else.

149
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:26,041
I see red!

150
00:11:26,125 --> 00:11:27,500
They're a Fairy Soldier!

151
00:11:27,583 --> 00:11:28,875
[FREE]
What?

152
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:32,583
I can't make out their
face from this distance.

153
00:11:38,583 --> 00:11:41,250
[KLARA gasps]

154
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:42,416
Is everything all right?

155
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:44,208
[KLARA]
Yes.

156
00:11:44,291 --> 00:11:48,083
Whoever that person is, they
were looking in this direction.

157
00:11:48,166 --> 00:11:49,958
Or rather, my fairy's...

158
00:11:50,041 --> 00:11:52,041
We may've been spotted.

159
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:53,500
What do you say we
rush the caravan,

160
00:11:53,583 --> 00:11:55,875
seize the merchandise,
and call it a night?

161
00:11:55,958 --> 00:11:57,958
We will only as a last resort.

162
00:11:58,041 --> 00:11:59,750
Hold.

163
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:01,291
Somethin' wrong?

164
00:12:01,375 --> 00:12:02,625
[WOLF]
No.

165
00:12:06,458 --> 00:12:08,333
Wait. One of them is moving.

166
00:12:08,416 --> 00:12:10,375
It's the Fairy Soldier.

167
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:14,916
[FREE]
On it.

168
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,500
Hey. We're going to ground
level to track them.

169
00:12:17,583 --> 00:12:19,500
[MARLYA] I'm... sorry.
Were you talking to me?

170
00:12:19,583 --> 00:12:21,833
[SERGE] We might be playing
right into their hands.

171
00:12:21,916 --> 00:12:25,083
Serge and Klara, stay here and
continue surveilling the plaza.

172
00:12:25,166 --> 00:12:26,916
Are you comin' or what?

173
00:12:44,083 --> 00:12:47,791
Huh. Years have passed,
and it's still the same.

174
00:12:47,875 --> 00:12:50,958
It looks like the ruins of
some destroyed large city.

175
00:12:51,041 --> 00:12:53,166
I take it you've been
to this place before?

176
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:54,916
When it was a war zone.

177
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,666
A long time ago.

178
00:13:00,125 --> 00:13:02,125
[FREE]
Where the hell did they go?

179
00:13:02,208 --> 00:13:03,166
Uh.

180
00:13:04,083 --> 00:13:06,416
[MARLYA]
These tracks are still fresh.

181
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:08,625
They're nearby.

182
00:13:08,708 --> 00:13:09,916
Wait up.

183
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:17,750
Then they come to a
sudden stop right here.

184
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:19,083
How?

185
00:13:22,083 --> 00:13:24,208
Someone just passed by.

186
00:13:24,291 --> 00:13:26,208
They might be backtracking.

187
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:27,666
What does that mean?

188
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:29,458
You see bears do it often.

189
00:13:29,541 --> 00:13:31,750
And other smart animals.

190
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,916
They walk back over
their own prints.

191
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,166
I get it.

192
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:38,000
While we run in circles,
they make their escape.

193
00:13:50,208 --> 00:13:51,666
[FREE, MARLYA panting]

194
00:13:57,458 --> 00:13:59,125
[FREE]
Move, Serge!

195
00:13:59,208 --> 00:14:00,666
[KLARA]
Get down!

196
00:14:09,875 --> 00:14:11,000
[FREE grunts]

197
00:14:13,416 --> 00:14:21,041
[gasps] It can't be!

198
00:14:21,125 --> 00:14:22,916
[FREE]
Wolfran!

199
00:14:27,041 --> 00:14:29,375
No. I should stay outta this.

200
00:14:31,875 --> 00:14:33,916
You're an errand boy
for the mafia?

201
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,750
How pathetic.

202
00:14:40,916 --> 00:14:44,416
What happened to you?
Answer me!

203
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:46,875
What does your family
think of you now?

204
00:14:46,958 --> 00:14:48,625
Your wife and your daughter?

205
00:14:48,708 --> 00:14:51,916
[WOLF] I see you still don't
know when to stop yapping.

206
00:15:01,125 --> 00:15:01,958
[FREE gasps]

207
00:15:02,041 --> 00:15:03,708
[gasps] Not good!

208
00:15:03,791 --> 00:15:05,666
[FREE]
Marlya!

209
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:06,916
[MARLYA grunts]

210
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:13,000
[FITCHER grunts]

211
00:15:13,083 --> 00:15:14,291
[MARLYA yelps]

212
00:15:18,041 --> 00:15:20,166
This fairy is...

213
00:15:23,458 --> 00:15:24,708
[groans]

214
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:27,750
Fall back, now!

215
00:15:27,833 --> 00:15:31,666
Hope you didn't forget
about me, sir!

216
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:32,708
[WOLF gasps]

217
00:15:35,291 --> 00:15:37,458
Weaklings like to swarm.

218
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:40,958
[FREE]
Damn it!

219
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:43,583
[FREE]
Uh.

220
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:49,916
Is it trying to protect her?

221
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:53,208
It's all right. He isn't
going to hurt me.

222
00:15:57,208 --> 00:16:01,208
[panting] What is this feeling?

223
00:16:01,291 --> 00:16:02,791
[FREE]
Can you stand?

224
00:16:02,875 --> 00:16:05,250
I think. [panting]

225
00:16:05,333 --> 00:16:06,791
Who is he?

226
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:09,166
We were comrades
during the great war.

227
00:16:09,250 --> 00:16:12,333
As long as I've known him,
he's been ruthless and cunning.

228
00:16:12,416 --> 00:16:14,333
Still, it isn't like him
to run from a fight.

229
00:16:14,416 --> 00:16:15,625
[SERGE]
Sir!

230
00:16:15,708 --> 00:16:17,166
Pursue the target!

231
00:16:17,250 --> 00:16:19,875
I'll cover you with sniper fire
while Klara spots for me!

232
00:16:19,958 --> 00:16:22,375
Then we're going to need
to relocate quickly!

233
00:16:22,458 --> 00:16:24,000
Lead the way.

234
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:26,291
You good to go?

235
00:16:26,375 --> 00:16:30,291
It's for the job,
right? I'm ready.

236
00:16:30,375 --> 00:16:31,791
Yes, ma'am.

237
00:16:35,666 --> 00:16:36,833
[BOTH gasp]

238
00:16:36,916 --> 00:16:38,833
Looks like our
operation is blown.

239
00:16:38,916 --> 00:16:41,625
Dorothea already knew
about the meeting place.

240
00:16:41,708 --> 00:16:43,541
So what're we
supposed to do now?

241
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:44,833
Call it off?

242
00:16:44,916 --> 00:16:46,291
We fight back.

243
00:16:46,375 --> 00:16:48,625
There's a sniper. Be careful.

244
00:16:48,708 --> 00:16:50,041
[IZEM]
They were meant to be sold,

245
00:16:50,125 --> 00:16:51,875
so only three are tuned up.

246
00:16:51,958 --> 00:16:53,416
[WOLF]
It'll be enough.

247
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:55,708
[whistle blows]

248
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:05,166
[FREE gasps]

249
00:17:17,125 --> 00:17:18,000
You okay?

250
00:17:18,083 --> 00:17:18,958
Just fine.

251
00:17:19,041 --> 00:17:20,083
Good.

252
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:26,666
There's three of them.

253
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:27,958
Why isn't it...?

254
00:17:28,041 --> 00:17:30,166
Your fairy took a lot
of damage back there.

255
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:31,083
It needs to rest.

256
00:17:31,166 --> 00:17:32,375
What should I do then?

257
00:17:32,458 --> 00:17:34,166
You provide covering fire.

258
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:35,583
They're not people.

259
00:17:35,666 --> 00:17:37,125
Shoot to kill!

260
00:17:48,916 --> 00:17:50,291
[FREE grunting]

261
00:17:56,416 --> 00:17:57,666
[gasps]

262
00:17:57,750 --> 00:18:00,708
Hitting it's no problem,
but where do I hit it?

263
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:05,875
Well, Wolfran?! Show yourself!

264
00:18:05,958 --> 00:18:07,625
Your range is 620.

265
00:18:07,708 --> 00:18:09,291
[SERGE]
Got it.

266
00:18:12,208 --> 00:18:13,708
[FREE grunts]

267
00:18:13,791 --> 00:18:15,041
Fire!

268
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:25,875
[MARLYA]
Huh? He kids around,

269
00:18:25,958 --> 00:18:28,291
but Serge is an incredible shot.

270
00:18:28,375 --> 00:18:29,708
[FREE grunts]

271
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:44,916
Get moving!

272
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:46,833
[MARLYA]
Yeah. That's a good idea!

273
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,833
Lose your nerve?

274
00:19:02,916 --> 00:19:04,625
Try me, creep.

275
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:14,250
Ironic, isn't it?

276
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:17,333
Facing each other
here of all places.

277
00:19:17,416 --> 00:19:20,333
You don't actually think
you can keep up with me.

278
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:32,541
[FREE grunts]

279
00:19:37,541 --> 00:19:40,291
[RED HOOD howls]

280
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:50,333
[IZEM grunting]

281
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:55,916
[WOLF]
So, you're not dead... Yet.

282
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:59,000
[IZEM]
Huh?!

283
00:19:59,083 --> 00:20:00,333
Why're you doin' this?

284
00:20:00,416 --> 00:20:02,416
I used to be a
soldier too, y'know.

285
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:04,875
If I was caught,
I wouldn't have talked.

286
00:20:04,958 --> 00:20:08,041
You have to believe me.

287
00:20:08,125 --> 00:20:10,458
They all say the same thing.

288
00:20:10,541 --> 00:20:12,666
--[IZEM gasps]
--Sorry.

289
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:14,541
[gunshot]

290
00:20:14,625 --> 00:20:17,333
[creaking]

291
00:20:24,208 --> 00:20:26,666
You're not getting away from me!

292
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:33,333
Marlya!

293
00:20:33,416 --> 00:20:35,583
Meet up with Klara and Serge!

294
00:20:35,666 --> 00:20:37,083
But!

295
00:20:37,875 --> 00:20:40,458
Think you can outrun
me with a transport?

296
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:48,250
Wolfran!

297
00:20:48,333 --> 00:20:49,916
Here goes nothing...

298
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:03,750
Start talkin', pal!

299
00:21:06,416 --> 00:21:08,708
Tell me who did this to you?

300
00:21:08,791 --> 00:21:10,083
Don't be stupid.

301
00:21:10,166 --> 00:21:12,208
Never should've trusted him.

302
00:21:20,750 --> 00:21:22,333
Damn...

303
00:21:25,708 --> 00:21:29,625
[FREE grunts, laughs]

304
00:21:29,708 --> 00:21:31,750
I don't know why I'm surprised.

305
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:35,333
Leave no trace behind, huh?

306
00:21:35,416 --> 00:21:39,583
Still thorough as ever, I see.

307
00:21:39,666 --> 00:21:42,750
All this time and he
hasn't changed one bit.

308
00:21:42,833 --> 00:21:45,000
So that's how you
want to play it?

309
00:23:35,541 --> 00:23:36,958
[exhales]

310
00:23:39,375 --> 00:23:40,500
[FREE]
Plenty of room.

311
00:23:40,583 --> 00:23:41,875
Enough to manufacture
artificial fairies.

312
00:23:41,958 --> 00:23:43,208
[MARCO]
Securing the <i>Black Fairy Tome</i>

313
00:23:43,291 --> 00:23:45,375
is a matter of grave
concern for us.

314
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:46,625
[MARLYA]
Don't move!

315
00:23:46,708 --> 00:23:48,458
[SWEETIE] Young lady,
you may call me Bitter.

